On the cover of The Pulse Magazine’s Trends and More edition is Mayur Hola, VP - Brand at Swiggy, an Advertising & Brand Leader who has shaped digital-first brands like OYO, Subway, and Swiggy.  In a candid conversation, he unpacks the key pillars of building a successful digital-first brand, ideal framework for storytelling and more!

This edition also brings together insights from top advertisers and marketers, offering a roadmap to navigate the ever-evolving industry. From trend forecasts to game-changing strategies, these pages serve as a guidebook for marketers planning the year ahead.

Read the cover story to discover how Mayur has built brands that have seamlessly integrated into our daily lives so much so that we can’t imagine a world without them.

The Pulse Magazine’s Festive Edition curates a playbook for Indian Advertising and Marketing Professionals. We understand the evolving dynamics of festive marketing, where tradition meets modernity and technology drives personalisation.

On the cover, we have Mr Sunder Balasubramanian, the Chief Marketing Officer of Myntra, a brand that has redefined fashion e-commerce in India. The conversation with Sunder delves into Myntra’s Festive Marketing strategies, their annual festive sale and initiatives to engage with the audience.

Read the cover story to know how Myntra taps into India’s festive spirit to deliver campaigns that resonate with millions.

latestPosts.caption:
This edition is our attempt to unpack, unlearn, and rewrite what it truly means to be a Superwoman not someone who’s flawless, but someone fearless in her flaws. A celebration of stories that challenge the status quo, embrace vulnerability, and redefine power on their own terms.

On our cover is the incomparable @bhattacharyaswati, Global Head of Lightbox Creative Lab at Godrej Consumer Products Limited.

A creative force. A relentless voice. The woman who showed the advertising world that emotional truth will always outshine a perfect brief. Swati doesn’t just create campaigns, she challenges conventions, shatters stereotypes, and sparks the conversations that truly matter.

Within these pages, you’ll find stories that examine the intersection of ambition, vulnerability, power, and choice.

Follow the link in bio to download the magazine.

latestPosts.caption:
Centraal Beheer’s legendary ad campaign, “Even Apeldoorn bellen,” (“Just Call Apeldoorn”) made a comeback with its 63rd commercial, “Scammers.” This was the first spot from new agency TBWA\Neboko after a 37-year partnership with DDB Unlimited. The new ad followed a young backpacker dealing with the fallout from a moment of distraction, blending humor with a modern twist on digital scams. The campaign, running since the mid-80s, stayed true to its roots, highlighting Centraal Beheer’s reputation for being accessible and ready to help in any crisis

Agency: TBWA\NEBOKO ( @tbwaneboko )
Brand: Centraal Beheer ( @centraalbeheer )
Director: Bart Timmer
Production House: CZAR Amsterdam ( @czar_amsterdam )

#CampaignSpot

latestPosts.caption:
On World Environment Day, here’s a throwback to Britannia’s OOH campaign, “Nature Shapes Britannia,” redefining advertising by letting nature guide the design. Billboards were crafted to bend and adapt to surrounding trees, showcasing the brand’s commitment to sustainability. 

Highlighting ESG milestones like plastic neutrality and water stewardship, the campaign used 100% biodegradable cotton for its billboards. Executed by Talented India, this innovative initiative spanned Hyderabad, Kolkata, Meerut, and Pune, proving that impactful advertising can align with environmental responsibility.

Brand: Britannia
Agency: Talented India

#WorldEnvironmentDay #CampaignThrowback

#AD To celebrate the success of its award-winning Jupiter 110, TVS has rolled out an all AI-powered campaign, a bold step that reflects the brand’s innovative spirit and deep connection with its customers.

@tvsjupiterofficial

In 2024, Zomato marked World Environment Day with a quirky ad promoting its goal of 100% electric vehicle (EV) deliveries by 2030. The film humorously showed delivery partners testing absurd transport methods like camels, pogo sticks, and paragliding before settling on EVs as the fastest, cleanest option. 

The company also highlighted its partnerships with 70+ EV rental firms and financial aid for drivers to switch to e-bikes. As part of its net-zero mission, Zomato aims to cut emissions from last-mile deliveries, a major chunk of its carbon footprint.

#WorldEnvironmentDay #CampaignThrowback
